{"questionId":"22871","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A large water reservoir is built in the form of part of an upside-down right pyramid with a horizontal square base of length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>80</mn></math> metres. The point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>C</mtext></math> is the centre of the square base and point <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>V</mtext></math> is the vertex of the pyramid.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/c25c3e486d3b74ace4d08c21a7d354a82a6c05c7.png\"></p>\n<p>The&nbsp;bottom of the reservoir is a square of length <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>60</mn></math> metres that is parallel to the base of the pyramid, such that the depth of the reservoir is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn></math> metres as shown in the diagram.</p>\n<p>The second diagram shows a vertical cross section, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>MNOPC</mtext></math>, of the reservoir.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:center;\"><img src=\"__IMG__/c943e2c9b5777abafc1f4c4ce840d396dc4a07d6.png\"></p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mtext>CV</mtext></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mtext>CV</mtext><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>40</mn><mo> </mo><mi>tan</mi><mfenced><mi>θ</mi></mfenced></math>&nbsp; <strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mtext>CV</mtext><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>×</mo><mn>6</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>(M1)</em></strong></p>\n<p><br><strong>Note:</strong> Award <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em> for an attempt at trigonometry or similar triangles (e.g. ratios).</p>\n<p><br><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mtext>CV</mtext><mo>=</mo></mrow></mfenced><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>24</mn><mo> </mo><mtext>m</mtext></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<strong><em>A1</em></strong></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22871","referenceCode":"21N.2.SL.TZ0.4b.i","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Find CV.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"b.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.1—3d space, volume, angles, midpoints","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.2—2d and 3d trig","Topic 3—Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.3—Angles of elevation and depression"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}